gobblin.writer

Class FsDataWriter<D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.writer.FsDataWriter<D>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SpeculativeAttemptAwareConstruct, FinalState, DataWriter<D>, MetadataAwareWriter, Closeable, AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AvroHdfsDataWriter, HiveWritableHdfsDataWriter, SimpleDataWriter

    public abstract class FsDataWriter<D>
extends Object
implements DataWriter<D>, FinalState, MetadataAwareWriter, SpeculativeAttemptAwareConstruct
    An implementation of DataWriter does the work of setting the output/staging dir and creating the FileSystem instance.

      • getDefaultMetadata

        public GlobalMetadata getDefaultMetadata()
        Description copied from interface: MetadataAwareWriter
        Get default metadata that will be attached to records that pass through this writer. For example, if the writer always gzip's data that passes through it, it would implement this method and return a new GlobalMetadata object record with transferEncoding: ['gzip']. This default metadata will be merged with the RecordWithMetadata that is added to each record by the source and converters in the pipeline.
        Specified by:
        getDefaultMetadata in interface MetadataAwareWriter

      • commit

        public void commit()
            throws IOException
        .

        This default implementation simply renames the staging file to the output file. If the output file already exists, it will delete it first before doing the renaming.

        Specified by:
